Stertinius appears to have been an authority among the Stoies of the day. The Scholiasts tell us he wrote 220 books on the doctrines of that school.

'Damasippus calls him (v. 296) “sapientum octavus.” His books, if he ever wrote them, have not rescued him from oblivion. Horace mentions him again, in Epp. i. 12. 20, as the representative of the sect.
